<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>HB04268</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : AN ACT AMENDING REPUBLIC ACT 7042, OTHERWISE KNOWN AS THE FOREIGN INVESTMENTS ACT OF 1991, TO AUGMENT FOREIGN INVESTMENT, TO PROMOTE SUPPLEMENTARY SOURCE OF REVENUE, AND FOR OTHER PURPOSES</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ABSTRACT : Intends to amend Sec.8 of R.A.No.7042, as amended by R.A.No.8179, to read as follows:

... "Small and medium-sized domestic market enterprises with paid-in equity capital less than the 
equivalent of $300,000.00, are reserved to Philippine national:

Provided that: 
1) they involve advanced technology as determined by the DOST;  or
                       
2) they employ at least 15 direct employees, then a minimum paid-in capital of $150,000.00
   shall be allowed to non-Philipppine nationals.

</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>ROMERO, MICHAEL ODYLON L.</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2019-08-29</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SIGNIFICANCE: NATIONAL</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE ON RULES</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>REFERRAL TO THE COMMITTEE ON ECONOMIC AFFAIRS ON 2019-09-04</td></tr></table>